comments:
I've duplicated this problem by trying to open a design that isn't within the current workspace.

From my investigation the problem looks to be caused by the fix for bug 136536

Comparing the code in MultiPageReportEditor init 

		IReportProvider provider = getProvider( );

		if ( provider != null && provider.getInputPath( input ) != null )
		{
			setPartName( provider.getInputPath( input ).lastSegment( ) );
			firePropertyChange( IWorkbenchPartConstants.PROP_PART_NAME );
		}
		else
		{
			setPartName( input.getName( ) );
			firePropertyChange( IWorkbenchPartConstants.PROP_PART_NAME );
		}


with that from addPages

		// For back compatible only.
		// Provide warning message to let user select if the auto convert needs
		// See bugzilla bug 136536 for detail.
		String fileName = getProvider( ).getInputPath( getEditorInput( ) )
				.toOSString( );


You can see that the init method checks that the provider can actually return the information before using it, but the addPages doesn't.

The underlying cause for the NPE is the FileReportProvider (returned by getProvider()) checking that the editor input is a IPathEditorInput, which it isn't if the editor input is created from a design outside of the workspace, and then returning null when asked for the path which fails when converting to an OSString.

The original root for this problem is the fact that org.eclipse.ui.ide.IDE.getEditorInput(IFileStore fileStore) is being used to create the EditorInput and returns a FileEditorInput if the design is in the workspace or a FileStoreEditorInput if the design isn't.

It would appear that either addPages needs to be updated to perform a similar check to init, or FileReportProvider.getInputPath should be updated to handle  IEditorInputs other than IPathEditorInput, or FileStoreEditorInput extended to support IPathEditorInput (the build I'm using it implements IURIEditorInput)
